==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin [[cucurbita]] ‘gourd’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /kju:kɜ:bɪ'teɪʃəs/

===Adjective===
'''cucurbitaceous'''
# pertaining to the [[gourd]] family, including [[cucumber]]s, [[pumpkin]]s etc.
#:*'''1973''': On he goes, gabbing, gabbing, recipes for preparing beets in a hundred tasty ways, or such '''cucurbitaceous''' improbabilities as Ernest Pudding’s Gourd Surprise — Thomas Pynchon, ''Gravity's Rainbow''